A vintage 1950s technical illustration showing a massive filing cabinet being fed into an elaborate brass and copper mechanical contraption with gears, pipes, and valves, transforming paper spreadsheet grids into neatly organized rows of punched cards emerging from the other side. The machine features Victorian-era industrial design elements with steam wisps rising from vents. Warm sepia and copper tones dominate the color palette, with dramatic shadows cast across a workshop floor. The style evokes old technical manuals and patent drawings, with cross-hatching details and aged paper texture throughout the composition.
